data.title: Two individuals apprehended following theft of $1.4M in Bitcoin from South Korean police custody in 2021; incident undetected for 4 years.
data.description: In 2021, law enforcement confiscated a significant amount of Bitcoin. The digital currency was placed in a separate wallet managed by a third party. However, unauthorized individuals were able to gain access to the wallet, resulting in the loss of the Bitcoin. This breach went unnoticed for a period of four years.
